author: Liz Raftery, TV GUIDE
title: Honey Boo Boo Just Released a Rap Video
text:
Honey Boo Boo Just Released a Rap Video 1 / 1 Back to Gallery 
Grab your Go-Go Juice - Honey Boo Boo just released a rap video. 
The 10-year-old star of Here Comes Honey Boo Boo has debuted a new song, "Movin' Up," under her real name, Alana Thompson. The video features Thompson bopping around with her mother, "Mama June" Shannon , Shannon's on-again-off-again boyfriend Mike "Sugar Bear" Thompson, and Alana's 16-year-old sister Lauryn (aka Pumpkin). 
"I'm just a small-town girl / Living in my princess world," Alana yells in the song's opening lines. 
The video is a sight to behold in itself, and the song is catchy, if nothing else. The clip was produced by viral video guru Adam Barta , who has previously collaborated with Margaret Cho , Anthony Weiner 's sexting partner Sydney Leathers, and "Tan Mom" Patricia Kentcil .
